Exor (company) - Wikipedia






















 






Exor (company)

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


Exor N.V.





Type

public N.V.


Traded as
BIT: EXO


ISIN
NL0012059018


Industry
Investment company


Founded
27 July 1927 (IFI)


Headquarters
Hoogoorddreef 15, 1101 BA Amsterdam



Key people

John Elkann (Chairman & CEO)


Revenue
€ 140.068 billion (2016)[1]


Profit
€ 22 billion (2016)[1]


Total assets
€ 176.528 million (2016)


Total equity
€ 30.220 million (2016)


Owner
Giovanni Agnelli B.V. (52.99%)



Number of employees

302,562 (2015)[2]


Website
www.exor.com


Exor N.V. is a leading[3] investment company, incorporated in The Netherlands and now controlled by Italy's Agnelli family. It has a capitalization of over $13 billion USD, with a history of investments running over a century. Its principal investments include Fiat Chrysler Automobiles, CNH Industrial and Ferrari. Resultantly, Exor is first as an economic group in Italy for sales volume, and the 19th in the world, according to 2016 Fortune Global 500 List.[3]



