Exor N.V.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 1:09 PM ET
Diversified Financial Services

Company Overview of Exor N.V.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Exor N.V., through its subsidiaries, operates as an investment company. It operates through Fiat Chrysler Automobiles, CNH Industrial, Ferrari, PartnerRe, Juventus Football Club, and the Holdings System segments. The company invests in companies that design, engineer, develop, manufacture, distribute, and sell passenger cars, light commercial vehicles, components, production systems, and related parts and services, as well as that provide Ferrari cars. It also invests in companies, which design, produce, and sell trucks, commercial vehicles, buses, specialty vehicles, agricultural and construction equipment, and engines and transmissions. In addition, the company invests in companies that pu...
Exor N.V., through its subsidiaries, operates as an investment company. It operates through Fiat Chrysler Automobiles, CNH Industrial, Ferrari, PartnerRe, Juventus Football Club, and the Holdings System segments. The company invests in companies that design, engineer, develop, manufacture, distribute, and sell passenger cars, light commercial vehicles, components, production systems, and related parts and services, as well as that provide Ferrari cars. It also invests in companies, which design, produce, and sell trucks, commercial vehicles, buses, specialty vehicles, agricultural and construction equipment, and engines and transmissions. In addition, the company invests in companies that publishes The Economist, a weekly magazine; manages professional football teams; and provides robotics technologies for the oil and gas industry. Further, it invests in companies, which provide reinsurance and certain specialty insurance lines, including property, casualty, motor, agriculture, aviation/space, catastrophe, credit/surety, engineering, energy, marine, mortality, longevity, and accident and health, and alternative risk products. The company has operations in Europe, North America, Central and South America, Africa, Asia, Australia, and Oceania. Exor N.V. is based in Amsterdam, the Netherlands. Exor N.V. is a subsidiary of Giovanni Agnelli B.V.
Detailed Description


